{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "PPO became the basis for one of the two main families of RL from Human Feedback (RLFH, 2022) approaches, allowing to align LLM to human preferences.",
    "In the first approach, a reward model is first trained on (human) ranked responses (i.e., preferences) for desired properties y (e.g., clarity of text, non-offensive text).",
    "Subsequently, the reward model is used within the PPO update to align a pre-trained LLM, encoding p(x), towards the properties y.",
    "Similarly to REIN-VENT, RLHF augments the reward with a penalty for drifting too far from the original distribution p(x).",
    "The more recent GRPO algorithm [34] (2024) computes the rewards for groups of LLM's responses, augmenting the PPO update with a reward baseline (i.e., computed across the group), without needing to train any additional value model."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The more recent GRPO algorithm [34] (2024) computes the rewards for groups of LLM's responses, augmenting the PPO update with a reward baseline (i.e., computed across the group), without needing to train any additional value model."
  ]
}